title: Update note about `mbid` in Developer's API.md
message:
Update note about `mbid` in Developer's API.md

The MBIDs ingested by Last.FM *used* to be the MusicBrainz IDs for
MusicBrainz Track entities. However, Tracks were renamed to Recordings
with the MusicBrainz NGS overhaul[1], but since no one was interested in
breaking all the files already tagged with MusicBrainz identifiers, the
tag continues to be "MusicBrainz Track ID"/mb-trackid.

Note that some time later, a new pseudo-entity for Tracks for
introduced. These are saved as "MusicBrainz Release Track
ID"/mb-releasetrackid, but are not ingested by Last.FM. Last.FM only
takes Recording MBIDs.

[1] https://wiki.musicbrainz.org/History:Next_Generation_Schema
